3 Definitions and classification
The term ‘SVT’ literally indicates tachycardia [atrial rates >100 beats per minute (b.p.m.) at rest], the mechanism of which involves tissue from the His bundle or above.2,3 Traditionally, SVT has been used to describe all kinds of tachycardias apart from ventricular tachycardias (VTs) and AF. It has therefore included tachycardias such as atrioventricular (AV) re-entry due to accessory connections, which is not, in

