Verapamil or diltiazem i.v. should be considered if vagal manoeuvres and adenosine fail.92,94À98
Beta-blockers (i.v. esmolol or metoprolol) should be considered if vagal manoeuvres and adenosine fail.97,99,100
Synchronized DC cardioversion is recommended when drug therapy fails to convert or control the tachycardia.87,88

