Recommendations for the therapy SVT in pregnancy Catheter ablation is recommended in symptomatic women with recurrent SVT who plan to become pregnant. Acute therapy Immediate electrical cardioversion is recommended for any tachycardia with haemodynamic instability. Vagal manoeuvres and, if these fail, adenosine are recommended for acute conversion of SVT. Chronic therapy During the ﬁrst trimester of pregnancy it is recommended to avoid all antiarrhythmic drugs, if possible.

